## Third-party acknowledgements

### 多源学术检索 (Multi-source academic retrieval)

The multi-source retrieval engine (`services/agent/app/sources/`) was designed and
built with reference to the **Frontier Review / 研域前沿综述** project by
**violetreay** (LINUX DO community), which pioneered the multi-source academic
search workflow (CORE / OpenAlex / EuropePMC / Crossref / Unpaywall / Semantic
Scholar / HAL / BASE fan-out) that inspired this integration.

violetreay is a contributor to this project; the multi-source retrieval capability
is contributed to Aria Review as "multi-source information collection" under the
project's MIT license.

Aria Review's implementation is an independent (clean-room) rewrite driven by the
public API documentation of each upstream source plus empirically verified source
behaviour; it does not vendor the upstream project's source files. The trust core
(safe PDF download → MinerU structured parsing → cite_check → provenance) remains
Aria Review's own contribution and is applied to all multi-source candidates.
